ZH: 我正在攒钱，为了买一辆新车。
EN: I am saving up to buy a new car.

ZH: 她每天攒钱，准备去旅行。
EN: She saves money every day in preparation for a trip.

ZH: 我要攒够1000美元才能买这个新手机。
EN: I need to save up $1000 in order to buy this new phone.

ZH: 他攒了一年的钱，终于买到了心仪已久的电脑。
EN: He saved up money for a year and finally bought the computer he had been longing for.

ZH: 她学会了攒钱，以便将来能够自己独立生活。
EN: She learned to save money so that she can live independently in the future.

ZH: 他攒了一笔钱，计划明年去欧洲旅行。
EN: He saved up a sum of money and plans to travel to Europe next year.

ZH: 我每月攒一点钱，以备不时之需。
EN: I save a little money every month for unexpected expenses.

ZH: 她每周攒一些零花钱，用来买喜欢的东西。
EN: She saves up some pocket money every week to buy things she likes.

ZH: 我们应该养成攒钱的好习惯，以备不时之需。
EN: We should develop the good habit of saving money for unexpected situations.

ZH: 攒钱需要坚持，不要三天打鱼两天晒网。
EN: Saving money requires persistence, don't fish one day and hang the net for two.

ZH: 我攒了一些钱，打算今年买一辆自行车。
EN: I saved up some money and plan to buy a bicycle this year.

ZH: 妈妈总是嘱咐我们攒钱，以便将来有个好的生活。
EN: Mom always tells us to save money for a better future.

ZH: 我把零钱都攒到一个瓶子里。
EN: I save up all my loose change in a jar.

ZH: 我攒了足够的钱，终于可以去看那场音乐会了。
EN: I saved up enough money and finally can go to see that concert.

ZH: 弟弟正在努力攒钱，想给爸爸妈妈买个礼物。
EN: My younger brother is working hard to save up money to buy a gift for our parents.

ZH: 他每天攒一点钱，打算明年去上海旅行。
EN: He saves a little money every day and plans to travel to Shanghai next year.

ZH: 为了攒钱，他每天都带便当上班。
EN: In order to save money, he brings his own lunch to work every day.

ZH: 攒钱不容易，但是值得。
EN: Saving money is not easy, but it's worth it.

ZH: 她攒了很多钱，买了一套房子。
EN: She saved up a lot of money and bought a house.

ZH: 我攒了一些零钱，打算买个新手机。
EN: I saved up some loose change and plan to buy a new phone.

ZH: 她正在攒钱，希望可以买到一件漂亮的衣服。
EN: She is saving up in the hopes of buying a beautiful dress.
